&nbsp;

Please find attached a Personal Tutor Toolkit that summarises the role of the Personal Tutor and provides some key information for signposting tutees.

&nbsp;

Below is an example structure of the kind of topics you may discuss with your tutees. Meetings are expected to take place 3 times in the academic year for level 1 undergraduates and taught postgraduate students and at least twice a year for levels 2-4. These may be programmed in your electronic staff timetable but if not you could check with your DSE or your SES team <a href="mailto:sso@comp.leeds.ac.uk">sso@comp.leeds.ac.uk</a>  as to which week personal tutorials take place in your school.

